<item>
            <title>[FLINK-8138] Race in TaskAsyncCallTest leads to test time out</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLINK-8138</link>
                <project id="12315522" key="FLINK">Flink</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;TaskAsyncCallTest#testSetsUserCodeClassLoader&lt;/tt&gt; times out with a stack trace on Travis on a personal branch with unrelated changes on top of 1.4.0 RC 0.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve attached the Travis output to this issue. The main thread is stuck in&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;main&quot;&lt;/span&gt; #1 prio=5 os_prio=0 tid=0x00007ff59000a000 nid=0xb9b in &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;Object&lt;/span&gt;.wait() [0x00007ff598965000]
   java.lang.&lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;Thread&lt;/span&gt;.State: WAITING (on object monitor)
	at java.lang.&lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;Object&lt;/span&gt;.wait(Native Method)
	- waiting on &amp;lt;0x00000000833994c8&amp;gt; (a java.lang.&lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;Object&lt;/span&gt;)
	at java.lang.&lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;Object&lt;/span&gt;.wait(&lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;Object&lt;/span&gt;.java:502)
	at org.apache.flink.core.testutils.OneShotLatch.await(OneShotLatch.java:56)
	- locked &amp;lt;0x00000000833994c8&amp;gt; (a java.lang.&lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;Object&lt;/span&gt;)
	at org.apache.flink.runtime.taskmanager.TaskAsyncCallTest.testSetsUserCodeClassLoader(TaskAsyncCallTest.java:201)
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There are no other Flink related threads alive.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
